$ tzutil.exe

*Windows → development/date-time/time-zone[Time Zone] Utility*

`tzutil /g` shows the time zone ID:
code {
C:\> tzutil /g
W. Europe Standard Time
code }

To set the current time zone to a given ID, the `/s` option must be used.

`/l` gets a list of all time zone displays names and their IDs

sa:
  The Unix shell utility → Linux/shell/commands/tzselect[`tzselect`]
